    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> kind Letters of the 8<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. &amp; 15<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. ins<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> met me here. I am quite angry at y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                    thinking of buying any of my works when you have such a just clame to all I can
                    do. but neither vol. can appear before the latter end of. next month.<note type="editorial">Both the third edition of Pennant's <bibl type="editorial">
                            <title ref="bi0004">
                                <hi rend="italic">Tour in Scotland
                                1769</hi>
                            </title>
                        </bibl> and the first edition of <bibl type="editorial">
                            <title ref="bi0008">his <hi rend="italic">Tour in
                                    Scotland and Hebrides 1772</hi>
                            </title>
                        </bibl> were published in
                        1774.</note> I hope to get <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0110">Johnstons poems</title>
                    </bibl> here; <sic>so do trouble yourself about
                        them</sic>. Be so good to peruse &amp; then forward the inclosed to
                        <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Low</persName>. I am
                    in much haste.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Dear Sir <lb/>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> most obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                    </salute>
                    <signed>
                        <persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName>
                    </signed>
                    <placeName ref="pl0699">London</placeName>
                </closer>
                <dateline>March. 21. 1774.</dateline>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Paton</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Custom House</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Edinburgh</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="underline">
                        <persName ref="pe0289">Walther Williams</persName>
                    </hi>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <stamp type="postmark">21/MR</stamp>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <stamp type="frank">FREE</stamp>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <stamp type="postmark">
                        <unclear reason="illegible">WR</unclear>
                    </stamp>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
